---
title: Puglia-Style Chicken Sausage Orecchiette with Roasted Tomato, Parmesan & Parsley
description: This simple, rustic pasta dish will take you straight to the heel of Italy’s boot–the Puglia region, where this dish is from. It stars burst tomatoes roasted with garlic and panko and a glossy olive-oil rich sauce. You’ll garnish it generously with Parmesan and parsley and there it is–an authentic Italian dinner in a quick 20 minutes–delizioso!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/664362e638584bf020f8c6b1-78efb006.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6644eafcf8c6b653637e5aa7-en-US.pdf
servings: 2
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Southern Europe
nutrition:
  calories: 1000 kcal
  fat: 50 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 85 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 45 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1260 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/puglia-style-chicken-sausage-orecchiette-6644eafcf8c6b653637e5aa7
time required: 20 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil.

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and minced). Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped).

Toss @grape tomatoes{8%ounce}, onion, garlic, and @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @salt{to taste}, and @pepper{to taste}.

Roast on top rack until tomatoes burst, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> Rinse shrimp under cold water, then pat dry with paper towels. Season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add shrimp or sausage; cook, stirring frequently, until cooked through, 4-6 minutes.

Once water is boiling, add @orecchiette pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain.

Return drained orecchiette to pot. Drizzle with @olive oil{3%tablespoon}.

Add roasted tomato mixture to pot with pasta; stir to combine, adding more olive oil a drizzle at a time if needed, until everything is coated in a glossy sauce. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> Stir pasta vigorously to prevent it from sticking together.

Stir @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} into pasta along with roasted tomato mixture.

Divide pasta between shallow #bowls{}. Garnish with @Parmesan cheese{6%tablespoon} and parsley. Serve.

> Chicken sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.